snippet.textDisplay: After staying here in South India, I've got to understand one thing which Gurdas Maan is trying to point to seemingly. It being that we  aren't proud of our culture and hence more deviating towards western culture and finding English and other languages more superior than Punjabi. If you consider Tamilians here in South India. They are really proud of their native language and culture. They carry their heritage well. I think it's high time we should learn this thing from them. It's really bad to disrespect your own mother tongue.
